-- Nomura Hires Taiwan Equities Business Head From Bank of America
-- B y   C i n d y   W a n g
-- 2013-09-04T04:02:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-04/nomura-hires-taiwan-equities-business-head-from-bank-of-america.html
Nomura Holdings Inc. hired Mei-yu
Shih from Bank of America Corp. to run equity sales and trading
in  Taiwan  as  Japan ’s biggest brokerage overhauls its Asia
equities business.  Shih, who will be based in Taipei, is a 12-year veteran of
Bank of America’s Merrill Lynch unit and had led its Taiwan
equity sales division since 2008, according to Aaron Pan, a Hong
Kong-based spokesman for Nomura.  Nomura hired Yasuhiro Fujiwara from Bank of America to lead
its Asia equities operations excluding Japan in March. Other
Bank of America executives to join the Japanese bank include
Stanley Wong, who joined as head of North Asia equity
distribution and Ajay Gupta, head of client trading for Asia
outside of Japan.  The new hire was announced yesterday by Wong in an internal
memo obtained by  Bloomberg News  and confirmed by Pan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cindy Wang in Taipei at 
